<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Fullerton women's gymnastics team has qualified for the NCAA 
championships for the second year in a row. 
</P>
<P>
The Titans (17-7) earned the bid by finishing second in the West Regional 
Saturday night at UCLA. UCLA gained an automatic berth by winning the meet. The 
NCAA championships are scheduled for Corvallis, Ore., April 20-21. 
</P>
