<P>
RICHARDS HOLDS EDGE AMONG DEMOCRATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A poll showed Ann Richards holding a slight lead over rival Jim Mattox as they 
campaigned for the final day before Tuesday's Democratic runoff for governor of 
Texas. 
</P>
<P>
The winner will face oilman-rancher Clayton W. Williams in the November 
election to succeed retiring Republican Gov. Bill Clements. The poll in 
Sunday's editions of the Dallas Morning News and the Houston Chronicle 
indicated Richards, 56, the state treasurer, was supported by 44% of Democrats 
who said they plan to vote. Mattox, 46, an ex-congressman and two-term attorney 
general, drew 38%, while 16% were undecided and 3% said they would not support 
either candidate. 
