<TEXT>
<P>
Bechtel Designing a Soviet Silicon Valley: The Soviet Union is turning to San 
Francisco-based Bechtel Group to study turning the research community of 
Troitsk, 20 miles south of Moscow, into a high-technology center. The Soviet 
government intends to spend $100 million each year to develop a network of such 
centers, Bechtel said. 
</P>
