<TEXT>
<P>
Suit Claims Defective Seat Belts in Hyundai Excels: The parents of a woman 
killed in a car crash in July filed a wrongful-death suit against the 
manufacturer of the Hyundai Excel in Los Angeles Superior Court Tuesday, 
claiming the car's seat belt was inadequate. 
</P>
<P>
James E. and Jeanine L. Mettee said their daughter, Lisa, had her seat belt 
fastened when she was hurled from her 1988 Excel in a roll-over accident. The 
"two-point seat belt in the car does not . . . restrain the pelvis and prevent 
the driver's ejection," the suit said. Hyundai declined comment. (Filed April 
3, 1990. Case No. C757210) 
</P>
</TEXT>
