<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Texas Instruments Inc. and Thai Airways have announced that they are jointly 
developing an advanced computer system dubbed EXPICS that will enhance the 
scheduling of flight operations. 
</P>
<P>
TI said it will provide engineering services, computer hardware and software, 
training and systems integration, while Thai will contribute experts in 
operations control, data processing and communications. 
</P>
<P>
The new system -- EXPert Irregularity Control System -- will use updated 
computer displays to alert controllers to disruptions in the flight schedule 
and allow them to quickly test various alternatives. 
</P>
<P>
TI said its agreement with Thai Airways will allow it to market the system to 
other carriers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
