PLAY BALL! They don't call it the national pastime for nothing. . . . More 
Americans play baseball and its little brother, softball, than any other sport 
in the nation. . . . The American Softball Assn. enrolled 226,000 teams in 
organized leagues last year -- an estimated 3 million players. . . . Santa Ana 
alone fielded 190 teams, mostly slo-pitch, with about 3,200 male and female 
players taking up every ball field in the city six days a week. Steve Emmons 
and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
