<TEXT>
<P>
STAMP OF GREATNESS: Tim Wallach grew up in Orange County and became an All-Star 
third baseman for the Montreal Expos. . . . Now Wallach is among the baseball 
players enshrined on postage stamps by the tiny Caribbean island of St. 
Vincent. . . . Why this honor from a British Commonwealth nation that prefers 
cricket? Because St. Vincent's stamps are printed by a New York firm that 
selects subjects titillating to stamp collectors. . . . Baseball is hot 
property, the firm says, but the sport "has no relevance at all to St. 
Vincent," said an island official. Steve Emmons and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
