ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STREET SHRINES: The season opens today (C1 and special Baseball '90 section, 
S1) but it's baseball year-round in northeast Placentia, where the streets are 
named after Hall-of-Famers Lou Gehrig, Ty Cobb, Ducky Medwick, Ted Williams, 
Stan Musial, Christy Mathewson and others. . . . Baseball stars are one of the 
official categories for Placentia street names, probably adopted by some 
long-forgotten sports fan, said Public Works Director Bob Hodson. . . . Next: 
streets named after famous athletes from Placentia, such as Olympic swimming 
gold medalist Janet Evans and tennis star Michael Chang. Steve Emmons and Mark 
I. Pinsky 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
