<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
CITY TO BUY PROPERTY FOR SENIORS COMPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has agreed unanimously to buy property on East Amerige Avenue 
for an apartment building for low-income senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
The owner, First Lutheran Church of Fullerton, has offered to sell the property 
for $750,000. 
</P>
<P>
The council, acting as the Redevelopment Agency, agreed to search for a 
developer willing to build up to 50 studio or one-bedroom apartments and keep 
the rents affordable for low- and moderate-income seniors for the life of the 
building. 
</P>
<P>
The city would sell the land at a discount and might agree to pay for other 
improvements at the site to attract a builder willing to keep rents low, 
redevelopment manager Terry M. Galvin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
