<P>
TITAN GYMNASTS ADVANCE TO NCAAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton's women's gymnastics team qualified for the NCAA 
championships for the second consecutive year, posting a season-high score of 
191.70 in the Western Regional at UCLA Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
The score, an average of 9.05 per event, was the fourth-best performance in 
Fullerton history, and gave the Titans a second-place finish to UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton will be the seventh-seeded team at the NCAA championships, April 
20-21 at Oregon State. 
</P>
