<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FRESNO STATE CRUISES PAST UC IRVINE, 5-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ranbir Grewal struck out eight to lead Fresno State to a 5-1 Big West 
Conference baseball victory over visiting UC Irvine Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters struck out 34 times in the three-game series, which Fresno State 
swept. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine committed eight errors, allowing four unearned runs. 
</P>
<P>
The only earned run by the Bulldogs (26-11, 6-0) came in the fourth inning on 
Chris Falco's solo home run. 
</P>
<P>
Shelby Niss' RBI single, which scored Chris Gallego, cut Fresno State's lead to 
2-1 in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Huber (5-2) took the loss for Irvine (23-16, 1-5), despite allowing only 
one earned run in seven innings. He walked one and struck out one. 
</P>
<P>
In the Cal State Hayward Softball Tournament quarterfinals: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 3, Chapman 1 -- Christy Wurster had three singles and Rose 
Connor had two hits, including an RBI double in the sixth for Chapman (33-13). 
Northridge scored three in the fifth, capitalizing on a double, a walk and 
three consecutive singles. 
</P>
