<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANNOUNCER TOM KELLY APPARENTLY SUFFERS HEART ATTACK AT COUNTRY CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Kelly, longtime USC radio and television announcer who is now with the 
Prime Ticket network, apparently suffered a heart attack early Sunday at the 
Riviera Country Club in Pacific Palisades, prior to a scheduled round of golf. 
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman at Saint John's Hospital in Santa Monica reported Sunday night 
that Kelly was in fair condition. 
</P>
<P>
According to Don Carlson, who was to play in Kelly's foursome, Kelly came out 
of the Riviera locker room into the clubhouse restaurant, sat down and said, 
"I'm having a heart attack." 
</P>
<P>
Carlson, who called paramedics, said Kelly was in considerable pain until after 
paramedics arrived and treated him. LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
