<TEXT>
<P>
Pop singer and songwriter Neil Sedaka, hospitalized since last week with an 
intestinal ailment, has decided to have surgery to correct the problem, 
hospital officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
"He is planning on surgery, but it has not been scheduled as yet," said Danbury 
Hospital spokesman Barth Keck. "Hopefully, it will be scheduled in the next 
week." 
</P>
<P>
Sedaka, 51, who lives in the affluent New York City suburb of Westport, Conn., 
was admitted to Danbury Hospital last Tuesday suffering from diverticulitis, an 
inflammation of the colon, hospital officials said. 
