PADRE HOME GUIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home park: San Diego Jack Murphy Stadium 
</P>
<P>
Location: 9449 Friars Road, San Diego, 92108. 
</P>
<P>
Phone numbers: 619-283-7294 or 619-283-4494 (weekends and game nights). 
</P>
<P>
Seating capacity: 59,022 
</P>
<P>
Year completed: 1967 
</P>
<P>
1989 attendance: 2,009,032 
</P>
<P>
Number of home dates: 80 
</P>
<P>
Average: 25,112 
</P>
<P>
Largest crowd, 1989: 52,883 (July 15 vs. Chicago) 
</P>
<P>
Record crowd, regular season: 54,732 (June 7, 1986 vs. Atlanta) 
</P>
<P>
Home run fences: Left and right fields 330 feet; left- and right-center 378; 
center 408. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket office hours: Gate C -- Monday through Friday, 9 a.m.-5 p.m.; 9 a.m. 
until start of game when team is in town. Advance ticket window: Gate C -- 
Monday through Saturday, 9 a.m. to 6 p.m.; 9 a.m. until after game when the 
team is in town. Tickets are also available at Teleseat locations. There are 12 
of them around San Diego County, and there is a service charge of $1.75 per 
ticket. 
</P>
<P>
Telephone orders: Call Teleseat at (619) 283-SEAT. Tickets can be charged on 
Visa or MasterCard. Tickets ordered seven days or more before the game will be 
mailed. Tickets ordered after that time will be available on game day at the 
Will Call window at Gate E two hours before game time. Teleseat phone lines are 
open 9 a.m. to 9 p.m. Monday through Friday and from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. on 
Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Mail orders: Orders must be received at least before the game. Include $3 per 
order for postage and handling. Mail orders to San Diego Padres, P.O. Box 2000, 
San Diego, 92120. Gift certificates also are available by mail and at the 
ticket office. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket prices: 
</P>
